---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About">
    <main>
        <h1>About</h1>

        <section>
            <h2>Technology Stack</h2>
            <p>
                This application demonstrates how to build a static site that can query and analyze Parquet files directly in the browser using:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Astro</strong> - A modern static site generator with excellent performance</li>
                <li><strong>DuckDB WASM</strong> - In-browser SQL analytics engine</li>
                <li><strong>Parquet</strong> - Efficient columnar storage format</li>
                <li><strong>Cloudflare R2</strong> - Object storage for hosting Parquet files</li>
                <li><strong>Cloudflare Pages</strong> - For hosting the static site</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>How It Works</h2>
            <p>
                The application works entirely client-side. When you load a page:
            </p>
            <ol>
                <li>DuckDB WASM is initialized in your browser</li>
                <li>Parquet files are fetched directly from Cloudflare R2</li>
                <li>SQL queries run directly in your browser against the Parquet data</li>
                <li>Results are displayed without requiring any server-side processing</li>
            </ol>
            <p>
                This architecture provides extremely fast analytics with no backend server required.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Getting Started</h2>
            <p>
                To use this project with your own data:
            </p>
            <ol>
                <li>Upload your Parquet files to Cloudflare R2</li>
                <li>Configure CORS settings on your R2 bucket to allow browser access</li>
                <li>Update the ParquetQuery components with your file URLs and custom SQL queries</li>
                <li>Deploy to Cloudflare Pages</li>
            </ol>
        </section>
    </main>
</Layout>

<style>
    main {
        margin: auto;
        padding: 1rem;
        width: 100%;
        max-width: 800px;
        color: #333;
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.6;
    }

    h1 {
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    h2 {
        font-size: 1.8rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
        color: var(--accent);
    }

    section {
        margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    }

    ul, ol {
        padding-left: 1.5rem;
        margin: 1rem 0;
    }

    li {
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
</style>
